<p><br>
<center><b><font size=+3>5.1 Component Integration</font></b></center>

<ol><b><font size=+1>Integrating Legacy Systems into Component-Based Systems</font></b>
<br>&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>
<font size=+1>No time and justification to replace existing legacy systems.</font></li>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>
<font size=+1>New functionality must be integrated with other components,
existing applications and data sources.</font></li>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>
<font size=+1>Does not allow time for total replacement.</font></li>
</ul>

<p><br><font size=+1>Component-Based software engineering aims at building
applications that are adaptable to business and technology chagnes, while
retaining legacy applications and legacy tecynology as far as possible
and reasonable.</font></ol>

